<paragraph id="B52CD60A357DFFC81924E818029FFA76" blockId="20.[826,1442,1388,1533]" pageId="20" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis id="87E70A18357DFFC81924E8180297FA0A" box="[826,952,1388,1409]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="40">Etymology:</emphasis>
The specific name is a noun in apposition and dedicated to arachnologist Jorge Iván Mendoza Marroquín for his participation in collecting the 
<typeStatus id="6A2868A8357DFFC81F6EE8DE048EFA34" box="[1392,1441,1450,1471]" pageId="20" pageNumber="40">type</typeStatus>
series, and his contribution to knowledge of the spiders of 
<collectingCountry id="CD84969A357DFFC81946E8930284FA76" box="[856,939,1511,1533]" name="Mexico" pageId="20" pageNumber="40">Mexico</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B52CD60A357DFFC81924EB52048EF89A" blockId="20.[826,1441,1573,1810]" pageId="20" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis id="87E70A18357DFFC81924EB52029FF9B0" box="[826,944,1574,1595]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="40">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Resembles 
<taxonomicName id="7293AD89357DFFC81E27EB520588F9B1" authorityName="Valdez-Mondragón &amp; Francke" authorityYear="2015" box="[1081,1191,1573,1595]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Ixchela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="20" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tlayuda">
<emphasis id="87E70A18357DFFC81E27EB520588F9B1" box="[1081,1191,1573,1595]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="40">I. tlayuda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but distinguished by the FAC long and rounded, forming an angle of 90° with the chelicerae in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="2DA8CA8F357DFFC81EC5EB170403F9F2" box="[1243,1324,1635,1657]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="20" pageNumber="40">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
); the VAF with sharp tip (
<figureCitation id="2DA8CA8F357DFFC819E6EBF50566F91C" box="[1016,1097,1665,1687]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="20" pageNumber="40">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
); the long, curved and sharp sub-distally sclerotized spine on ventral part of embolus (arrow, 
<figureCitation id="2DA8CA8F357DFFC8198DEBCA02CCF95F" box="[915,995,1726,1748]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="20" pageNumber="40">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
); and the epigynum with three projections apically, the central markedly longer and curved, the lateral ones small and rounded (
<figureCitation id="2DA8CA8F357DFFC81EF9EB8804BBF89A" box="[1255,1428,1787,1810]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="20" pageNumber="40">Figs 64, 66, 67</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B52CD60A357DFFC91924EA4F01FAFB1B" blockId="20.[826,1442,1850,1903]" lastBlockId="21.[144,759,198,1688]" lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="41" pageId="20" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis id="87E70A18357DFFC81924EA4F05CEF8DB" box="[826,1249,1850,1872]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="40">
Description: Male (
<typeStatus id="6A2868A8357DFFC81E16EA4E0545F8C4" box="[1032,1130,1850,1871]" pageId="20" pageNumber="40">Holotype</typeStatus>
). Prosoma:
</emphasis>
Pale yellow, with three brown markings on each side (
<figureCitation id="2DA8CA8F357DFFC81EF2EA2D0412F8E4" box="[1260,1341,1881,1903]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="20" pageNumber="40">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
). Ocular region pale yellow, with a brown longitudinal line projecting from AME (
<figureCitation id="2DA8CA8F357CFFC91B7DED90009BFF71" box="[355,436,228,250]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
). Fovea surrounded with an irregular, wide brown region, extending backward (
<figureCitation id="2DA8CA8F357CFFC91A89EC5601CAFEBC" box="[151,229,289,312]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
). Clypeus pale yellow, with a wide brown region near chelicerae (
<figureCitation id="2DA8CA8F357CFFC91B5BEC3400BDFEDD" box="[325,402,320,342]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
). Chelicerae brown, pale around the SAC (
<figureCitation id="2DA8CA8F357CFFC91B1DEC2B007BFEFE" box="[259,340,351,373]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
). Sternum pale yellow. Labium and endites brown; endites with retrolateral apophysis, which has a small subdistal protuberance. 
<emphasis id="87E70A18357CFFC91828ECE9035FFE39" box="[566,624,413,434]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Legs:</emphasis>
Coxae pale yellow, with small brown markings on retrolateral and prolateral parts. Trochanters pale yellow. Femora pale orange, with several brown rings throughout their length, one sub-distal ring dark brown, wide, very marked. Patellae brown. Tibiae pale orange, with several brown rings throughout their length, less visible than on femora. Metatarsi and tarsi orange, without colour rings. Legs with numerous oblique, long setae; with few short, vertical setae. 
<emphasis id="87E70A18357CFFC91BB3EFDB0369FD4F" box="[429,582,687,708]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Opisthosoma:</emphasis>
Conical, longer than high, pale blue, with dorsal grey pattern (
<figureCitation id="2DA8CA8F357CFFC91881EFBA0180FC89" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Figs 56, 57</figureCitation>
). Gonopore plate oval. 
<emphasis id="87E70A18357CFFC91BD4EF980329FC8A" box="[458,518,748,769]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Palp:</emphasis>
Femur pale yellow, conical, with several long setae ventrally; VAF conical, with sharp tip (
<figureCitation id="2DA8CA8F357CFFC91B4FEE5E00F8FCCB" box="[337,471,810,832]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Figs 60, 61</figureCitation>
). Patella and tibia pale orange. Procursus brown, long and straight, with distal spine, thin and curved (
<figureCitation id="2DA8CA8F357CFFC91B86EE13033CFCF6" box="[408,531,871,893]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Figs 60, 61</figureCitation>
). VPP with 3–4 long setae (
<figureCitation id="2DA8CA8F357CFFC91AC7EEF10007FC10" box="[217,296,901,923]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
). Embolus conical, dorsally with a curved spine (
<figureCitation id="2DA8CA8F357CFFC91AC2EED00073FC31" box="[220,348,932,954]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Figs 60, 61</figureCitation>
), ventrally with apical sigmoid projection (
<figureCitation id="2DA8CA8F357CFFC91AECEEB70055FC52" box="[242,378,963,985]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Figs 60, 61</figureCitation>
). PAB wide (
<figureCitation id="2DA8CA8F357CFFC91800EEB7035DFC52" box="[542,626,963,985]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="87E70A18357CFFC91895EEB701F8FC7C" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Measurements:</emphasis>
Total length 6.40. Carapace 2.45 long, 2.30 wide. Clypeus 0.95 long. Diameter AME 0.14, ALE 0.22, PME 0.17, PLE 0.20. Distance ALE–PME 0.17, PME–PME 0.26. Leg I: 45.31 (11.75 + 1.07 + 11.87 + 15.62 + 5.00), tibia II: 8.40, tibia III: 6.25, tibia IV: 8.30. Tibia I l/d: 31.50.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B52CD60A357CFFC91AB6E9ED03A0F91C" blockId="21.[144,759,198,1688]" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="87E70A18357CFFC91AB6E9ED00A9FB25" box="[168,390,1177,1198]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">
Female (
<typeStatus id="6A2868A8357CFFC91B11E9ED0056FB25" box="[271,377,1177,1198]" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Paratype</typeStatus>
).
</emphasis>
Similar to the male, but with the following differences: 
<emphasis id="87E70A18357CFFC91BA0E9CC0308FB46" box="[446,551,1208,1229]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Prosoma:</emphasis>
The three brown markings larger and darker than on male. Clypeus with brown region longer than on male, forming an upside down, U-shaped area. 
<emphasis id="87E70A18357CFFC91B97E86000EDFAA2" box="[393,450,1300,1321]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Legs:</emphasis>
The brown rings on femora and tibiae slightly more marked than on male. 
<taxonomicName id="7293AD89357CFFC91A8EE8250077FAED" authority=": Wider" authorityName="Wider" box="[144,344,1360,1382]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Epigynum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="21" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="87E70A18357CFFC91A8EE8250024FAED" box="[144,267,1361,1382]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Epigynum:</emphasis>
Wider
</taxonomicName>
than long, with three projections at apex (
<figureCitation id="2DA8CA8F357CFFC91AC7E81B00A4FA0E" box="[217,395,1391,1413]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Figs 64, 66, 67</figureCitation>
), with a small rounded pit on central projection (
<figureCitation id="2DA8CA8F357CFFC91B6FE8FA00ECFA28" box="[369,451,1421,1444]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Fig. 64</figureCitation>
). PP small (
<figureCitation id="2DA8CA8F357CFFC91847E8FA0385FA28" box="[601,682,1421,1444]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Fig. 65</figureCitation>
); with small, oval sac-shaped concavities between MSE and PP (
<figureCitation id="2DA8CA8F357CFFC91AE0E8BF007CFA6A" box="[254,339,1483,1505]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Fig. 65</figureCitation>
). MSE with upside down Y-shape (
<figureCitation id="2DA8CA8F357CFFC91A86E89D01C6FA74" box="[152,233,1513,1535]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Fig. 65</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="87E70A18357CFFC91AE1E89E0085FA74" box="[255,426,1514,1535]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Measurements:</emphasis>
Total length 5.40. Carapace 2.15 long, 2.10 wide. Clypeus 0.80 long. Diameter AME 0.10, ALE 0.22, PME 0.18, PLE 0.21. Distance ALE–PME 0.16. PME–PME 0.24. Leg I: 31.97 (8.70 + 1.00 + 8.90 + 10.37 + 3.00), tibia II: 6.40, tibia III: missing, tibia IV: 6.50; tibia I l/d 28.40.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B52CD60A357CFFC91A8EEBCB00E8F8E5" blockId="21.[144,759,1727,1902]" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="87E70A18357CFFC91A8EEBCB0065F95F" box="[144,330,1727,1748]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Natural history:</emphasis>
The specimens were collected in an oak forest, the females on their irregular sheet webs among boulders on the ground; the male 
<typeStatus id="6A2868A8357CFFC9187AEB8903ECF898" box="[612,707,1789,1811]" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">holotype</typeStatus>
was collected on an irregular sheet web in a corner inside a cabin, being the first specimen of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="7293AD89357CFFC918BBEA4E03D8F8C4" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2000" box="[677,759,1850,1871]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Ixchela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="21" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="87E70A18357CFFC918BBEA4E03D8F8C4" box="[677,759,1850,1871]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Ixchela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected inside a building.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B52CD60A357CFFC91938EDB105D5FF57" blockId="21.[806,1274,197,220]" box="[806,1274,197,220]" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="87E70A18357CFFC91938EDB105A5FF51" box="[806,1162,197,219]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">
Distribution: 
<collectingCountry id="CD84969A357CFFC919DCEDB20503FF50" box="[962,1068,198,219]" name="Mexico" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">MEXICO</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="775718E8357CFFC91E22EDB105A5FF51" box="[1084,1162,197,218]" country="Mexico" name="Puebla" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Puebla</collectingRegion>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="2DA8CA8F357CFFC91E82EDB105C1FF57" box="[1180,1262,197,220]" captionStart="Figure 90" captionStartId="19.[144,223,1055,1074]" captionTargetBox="[144,1424,196,1022]" captionTargetId="figure-394@19.[144,1424,196,1022]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 90. Known records of Ixchela azteca sp. nov., Ixchela jalisco sp. nov., Ixchela mendozai sp. nov., Ixchela purepecha sp. nov. and Ixchela tlayuda sp. nov." pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Fig. 90</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
